# Increment completion (single-contributor)

Do not start a new PR while any open PRs remain. An increment is **not done** until every item below is true.

## Before a new PR

- [ ] `gh pr list --state open` is empty (merge or close superseded PRs first)

## Increment checklist (do not end turn early)

1. [ ] **No open PRs** — all prior PRs merged or closed
2. [ ] **Sub-agent review** — run code review on the branch/diff; address findings
3. [ ] **PR exists** — create or update PR for this increment (before or after review is OK)
4. [ ] **Review fixes pushed** — findings fixed and committed to the PR branch
5. [ ] **CI green** — `gh pr checks <n>` until pass; fix failures before returning

## End of increment: next task

Do **not** end the turn without stating the next task.

- State what the **next increment** should be.
- If multiple options exist, pick the **preferred** one and say why briefly.
- Independent subtasks may run in **parallel sub-agents**, but **one PR** for the combined result (same checklist: no open PRs first, review, fix, CI green, merge).

Return a **Next task** section: preferred increment plus parallel sub-agent lanes (if any) within that single PR.

## Stop condition

- Only stop when CI passes on the **merged** work, or on a PR that is ready to merge and CI is green.
- If CI cannot pass, return with a **specific blocker** (check name, error, link) — do not silently stop.

## Quick commands

```bash
gh pr list --state open
gh pr checks <PR_NUMBER>
gh pr merge <PR_NUMBER> --squash   # or repo default
```
